27:35.354 --> 27:38.055
Nothing. It's just a long day.

27:41.293 --> 27:43.594
It's Scott, okay?

27:43.596 --> 27:45.796
I feel like...
I feel like

27:45.798 --> 27:47.798
he's using his position
to get back at me.

27:47.800 --> 27:49.366
Get back at you how?

27:49.368 --> 27:51.869
By investigating the 13th
for misconduct.

27:51.871 --> 27:54.838
Look, I know it's his job,
I just feel like, I don't know,

27:54.840 --> 27:55.973
he's making it personal.

27:55.975 --> 27:57.708
<i>Qué idiota.</i>

27:57.710 --> 28:00.477
What does gideon

28:00.479 --> 28:02.379
have to say about it?
- Gideon?

28:02.381 --> 28:04.782
You're calling him gideon?

28:04.784 --> 28:06.383
He's not <i> my</i> boss.

28:06.385 --> 28:08.786
Also, he likes my cooking.
That makes us friends.

28:09.722 --> 28:10.788
Well?

28:10.790 --> 28:13.724
Gideon has his own battles
to fight.

28:13.726 --> 28:16.427
Then he's lucky
to have you by his side.

28:17.797 --> 28:19.063
<i>Mi cubanita fuerte.</i>

28:26.072 --> 28:27.504
Detective Murphy.

28:27.506 --> 28:29.640
<i>Detective,
it's Diana ruiz, Robert's wife.</i>

28:29.642 --> 28:30.874
<i>Something's happened.</i>

28:30.876 --> 28:32.676
<i>He went out, left me a message</i>

28:32.678 --> 28:34.144
<i>saying if anything
happened to him</i>

28:34.146 --> 28:35.913
that he loved me,
that I should kiss Maya for him.

28:35.915 --> 28:37.081
<i>Where is he now?</i>

28:37.083 --> 28:38.682
I don't know.
That's why I called.

28:38.684 --> 28:39.917
<i>Okay, I'm on my way.</i>

28:42.054 --> 28:43.220
<i>Murphy.</i>

28:43.222 --> 28:45.756
Gideon, it's me.
We have a problem.

28:45.758 --> 28:47.458
I'll be back.

28:50.062 --> 28:51.395
<i>Thank you so much for coming.</i>

28:51.397 --> 28:54.164
Did he tell you anything else,
anything that might help us?

28:54.166 --> 28:56.066
No. He was in here
before he left.

28:56.068 --> 28:57.434
He was on the computer.

28:57.436 --> 28:59.236
Yes, which is
password-protected.

28:59.238 --> 29:01.271
Can you, I don't
know, hack it?

29:01.273 --> 29:02.840
Well, man as smart as Robert,

29:02.842 --> 29:04.274
that's, uh, not that simple.

29:04.276 --> 29:05.442
Please. I know him.

29:05.444 --> 29:06.610
He was talking
like he's desperate.

29:06.612 --> 29:08.445
We need to do something.

29:08.447 --> 29:09.847
I know, I know, I know that.

29:09.849 --> 29:12.683
C-could I take
this computer?
- Yes.

29:12.685 --> 29:14.451
Ada, I need you to get
down to the station now,

29:14.453 --> 29:16.787
with Pete and,
uh... computers.

29:16.789 --> 29:18.689
Which computers?
All the computers.

29:18.691 --> 29:21.625
I need to bypass some
pretty serious encryption. Go.

29:21.627 --> 29:23.594
Gideon, we let
him out of jail.

29:23.596 --> 29:26.096
If anything happens...
I know. Just drive.

29:34.740 --> 29:37.474
Bernie, my love, can you
connect me to Conrad, please?

29:37.476 --> 29:41.378
<i>Captain's busy.
Something I can do for you?</i>

29:41.380 --> 29:42.913
No. It's-it's important.

29:42.915 --> 29:45.215
He's got us working this
federal fugitive thing.

29:45.217 --> 29:48.152
You want me to leave him
another message?

29:48.154 --> 29:49.486
No, I have to talk to somebody.

29:49.488 --> 29:50.988
Well, you can either schedule
an appointment

29:50.990 --> 29:53.724
to talk with a shrink, or you
can keep talking. I'm all ears.

29:54.560 --> 29:56.160
All right.
The thing is,

29:56.162 --> 29:57.995
we found the guy,
and we-we thought

29:57.997 --> 30:00.264
he was kind of this,
you know, drug trafficker,

30:00.266 --> 30:01.799
but it turns out he was...

30:01.801 --> 30:03.834
He was stealing aids drugs
for poor people.

30:03.836 --> 30:05.169
That's his story?

30:05.171 --> 30:06.837
<i>Yeah. We checked it out.</i>

30:06.839 --> 30:08.939
I mean, he was in Texas,
he hit some hospital,

30:08.941 --> 30:10.440
took, like, 400 grand
worth of meds.

30:10.442 --> 30:12.176
People were dying.
They were just gonna throw

30:12.178 --> 30:13.443
those drugs away...
That's enough.

30:13.445 --> 30:15.646
Anyway, the guy's been
working at this clinic

30:15.648 --> 30:17.247
for, like, ten years.

30:17.249 --> 30:19.516
He's changing bedpans
and stuff, no problems.

30:19.518 --> 30:22.186
I-I guess we can bring
the guy in. It's just...

30:22.188 --> 30:24.254
<i>Captain tell you
to bring him in?</i>

30:25.357 --> 30:26.523
Yes.

30:26.525 --> 30:27.991
Then bring him in.

30:36.635 --> 30:37.968
Just thinking,

30:37.970 --> 30:39.803
I know I'm a rookie
and all, but...

30:39.805 --> 30:41.939
Maybe we should do
a perimeter check.

30:46.545 --> 30:48.745
Good call, rook.

30:50.282 --> 30:52.382
He's running an aes
256-bit. We can't get in

30:52.384 --> 30:54.117
this way unless you have
a friend at the NSA.

30:54.119 --> 30:55.719
Gideon, do you think...
Yeah, yeah, yeah, working on it.

30:55.721 --> 30:59.623
If the front door's locked,
might as well try the back.

30:59.625 --> 31:01.491
There's no fde
on his backup drive,

31:01.493 --> 31:03.794
so a regex scan
of the plaintext,

31:03.796 --> 31:05.562
it might turn up
the crypto-key.
- No.

31:05.564 --> 31:06.797
It might turn up the cryp...

31:06.799 --> 31:08.332
Check it out!
- Okay, fine.

31:08.334 --> 31:09.833
Oh, wait, you're right.

31:09.835 --> 31:11.068
It unlocked the encryption.

31:11.070 --> 31:12.069
Sorry for yelling.

31:12.071 --> 31:13.403
Ooh, yeah, looks like

31:13.405 --> 31:15.405
he got a lot of his information
from us here.

31:15.407 --> 31:16.740
Police scanner.

31:16.742 --> 31:18.075
Probably the smart move.

31:18.077 --> 31:19.476
He also put a tracking device
on Cruz's car.

31:19.478 --> 31:21.912
There's a lot of GPS data here.
Cool.

31:21.914 --> 31:23.914
Put it up on the board.
Okay, this data's a mess.

31:23.916 --> 31:25.682
I'm trying to piece it together.

31:25.684 --> 31:27.684
Well, maybe you should
invent digital duct tape.
"Maybe you should..."

31:27.686 --> 31:29.253
Actually,
that's a pretty good idea.

31:29.255 --> 31:30.420
Okay.

31:30.422 --> 31:31.755
There. That's where
the path stops.

31:31.757 --> 31:32.890
That's where he stopped tracking

31:32.892 --> 31:34.524
and he shut down
around 35 minutes ago.

31:34.526 --> 31:36.660
All right, I'm on it.
Send backup.

31:55.080 --> 31:56.780
The hell is this?

31:56.782 --> 31:59.583
All we know is Robert
tracked marcos' crews here.

31:59.585 --> 32:01.118
He own the place?

32:01.120 --> 32:03.654
No, the city does.
It's condemned.

32:04.890 --> 32:06.957
See those chlorine
containers?

32:06.959 --> 32:08.458
Sure looks like
someone's been using it.

32:08.460 --> 32:10.794
Probably where
they're cooking the junk.

32:10.796 --> 32:13.363
Either that or swimming
in a spacious indoor pool.

32:15.067 --> 32:16.300
We know what Robert drives?

32:16.302 --> 32:18.468
Hybrid, according
to his wife, but...

32:18.470 --> 32:20.804
I don't see one here.

32:20.806 --> 32:21.972
Gideon,

32:21.974 --> 32:23.707
<i>do you want to check out back?</i>
On it.

32:31.884 --> 32:34.484
All righty. I spy

32:34.486 --> 32:36.553
with my hd eye...

32:36.555 --> 32:38.789
There it is.

32:48.100 --> 32:49.967
It's registered to Robert.

32:54.006 --> 32:55.906
There's ammo
in the passenger seat.

32:55.908 --> 32:58.742
Looks like ruiz decided to do
a little amateur cop work.

32:58.744 --> 33:00.277
Damn it.

33:00.279 --> 33:02.346
We got to get in there now.

33:12.291 --> 33:14.024
Oh, hold on, murph.

33:14.026 --> 33:16.259
I mean, you know
I'm up for just about anything,

33:16.261 --> 33:18.362
but it's pitch black.
We don't have the first idea

33:18.364 --> 33:20.197
where anybody is in there.
And we go in

33:20.199 --> 33:21.665
with flashlights,
they'll see us coming.

33:22.634 --> 33:23.967
The glasses.

33:23.969 --> 33:25.602
The ones used
to see the marker dye.

33:25.604 --> 33:26.803
You still have yours?

33:26.805 --> 33:28.472
Yeah.
- Gideon,

33:28.474 --> 33:29.539
<i>those glasses you gave us...</i>

33:29.541 --> 33:30.707
<i>How are they at seeing
in the dark?</i>

33:30.709 --> 33:31.708
Great.

33:31.710 --> 33:32.776
Just-just... just have to

33:32.778 --> 33:33.810
change a few settings.

33:33.812 --> 33:36.279
<i>Okay, make it happen.</i>

34:01.907 --> 34:03.907
You've been on my ass for weeks!

34:03.909 --> 34:05.876
My daughter.
You hurt my daughter.

34:05.878 --> 34:07.377
You blame me for that?

34:07.379 --> 34:09.746
Then you come down here
with this gun,

34:09.748 --> 34:10.981
you try to take me out?

34:10.983 --> 34:14.284
<i>You ever even seen a gun,
old man? Here.</i>

34:14.920 --> 34:17.020
Let me show you.

34:17.022 --> 34:18.255
Police! Don't move!

34:18.257 --> 34:20.157
Back off!
- What the hell?

34:21.092 --> 34:22.859
Let him go, marcos.

34:22.860 --> 34:24.094
That ain't happening.

34:24.096 --> 34:26.329
- Back off or he dies.
- Calm down.

34:26.331 --> 34:28.864
<i>I'll calm down
when you back the hell off.</i>

34:28.867 --> 34:32.002
<i>Gideon, this just turned into
a hostage situation.</i>

34:37.076 --> 34:40.377
Be smart, Cruz.
You ain't walking out of here.

34:40.379 --> 34:41.945
Yeah? We'll see.

34:41.947 --> 34:44.781
Back off or I swear
I'll drop his ass.

34:44.783 --> 34:46.349
Gideon, we need to
do something here.

34:46.351 --> 34:48.685
<i>Calm down, marcos.
Just calm down.</i>

34:48.687 --> 34:50.520
Wait, why can't Brandt
just tase them both?

34:50.522 --> 34:53.723
It's not safe. We need
to call in a hostage negotiator.

34:53.725 --> 34:55.058
How long is
that gonna take?

34:55.060 --> 34:57.127
Half an hour.

34:57.129 --> 34:59.196
My guess is that's about
29 minutes too long.

34:59.198 --> 35:00.297
<i>Please.</i>

35:00.299 --> 35:02.032
Don't put yourself
in danger for me.

35:02.034 --> 35:03.200
This is my fight.

35:03.202 --> 35:04.634
Yeah.

35:04.636 --> 35:06.269
Maybe you should
listen to him.

35:06.271 --> 35:07.471
How about this:

35:07.473 --> 35:10.941
You let him go, we'll leave.

35:10.943 --> 35:12.142
You got my word.

35:12.144 --> 35:15.145
No. I walk out of here...

35:15.147 --> 35:16.580
Then he's free.

35:16.582 --> 35:18.215
<i>Otherwise he dies now.</i>

35:18.217 --> 35:19.649
Damn it.

35:19.651 --> 35:21.751
We can't let that
son of a bitch walk.

35:21.753 --> 35:22.986
Murphy, is there
any way that you can,

35:22.988 --> 35:24.754
you can get in there
and back Brandt up?

35:24.756 --> 35:27.724
Just let him go, marcos.
Not unless I'm shooting
through the wall.

35:29.561 --> 35:31.661
What if you did
shoot through the wall?

35:31.663 --> 35:33.763
I'm done with this.
Gideon, are you crazy?

35:33.765 --> 35:35.332
I can shoot anyone.

35:35.334 --> 35:37.167
Well, what if I can help?
What...

35:37.169 --> 35:40.637
What if I can show you
what Brandt is seeing?

35:40.639 --> 35:42.339
How?

35:42.341 --> 35:43.607
Just-just hang on a second. Ada.

35:43.609 --> 35:44.908
Yeah, I'm switching
the feeds now.

35:44.910 --> 35:46.343
<i>Let's figure this out.</i>

35:46.345 --> 35:47.844
We can't figure anything out!

35:47.846 --> 35:49.479
Okay, let's just
talk about this.

35:49.481 --> 35:51.681
Yeah? Yeah, you want
to talk about this now?

35:51.683 --> 35:54.084
Or after I paint the walls
with his brains?

35:54.086 --> 35:56.086
<i>See that pipe
he's standing under?</i>

35:56.088 --> 35:57.587
<i>I see it.</i>

35:57.589 --> 35:59.589
I'm not messing around.

35:59.591 --> 36:00.657
Get back!

36:06.965 --> 36:09.366
Gideon, I can't do this.
I'll be shooting blind.

36:09.368 --> 36:11.034
Just trust the tech.

36:11.036 --> 36:13.103
Nobody's messing with you.

36:13.105 --> 36:15.172
Just lower the gun.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.042
I'm done with this.

36:19.044 --> 36:22.512
I want you and the rest of
the cops out of here now.

36:22.514 --> 36:24.281
What if I can't?

36:24.283 --> 36:26.783
Well, then just trust me.

36:26.785 --> 36:28.518
<i>Switch your gun to lethal.</i>

36:28.520 --> 36:30.353
The quicker
you let him go,

36:30.355 --> 36:31.721
the quicker
we'll be out of here.

36:31.723 --> 36:32.722
You better back off!

36:32.724 --> 36:34.057
This is your last chance.

36:34.059 --> 36:36.226
Listen to me carefully, marcos.

36:36.228 --> 36:37.894
It's not too late
to turn this thing around.

36:37.896 --> 36:39.563
You got him.

36:39.565 --> 36:41.798
We can figure something out.

36:41.800 --> 36:42.899
No!

36:42.901 --> 36:44.968
No, we can't!

36:59.685 --> 37:01.251
Police! Don't move!

37:01.253 --> 37:03.320
Don't move.

37:09.094 --> 37:11.061
He's alive.

37:20.439 --> 37:22.672
<i>Thank you.</i>

37:34.786 --> 37:36.786
<i>What the hell do you mean</i>

37:36.788 --> 37:38.722
Reggie Walker escaped?

37:38.724 --> 37:39.956
Uh, well,

37:39.958 --> 37:40.957
it was crazy, sir.

37:40.959 --> 37:42.759
Uh, we were
questioning him, and, uh,

37:42.761 --> 37:46.096
and then, uh, fearing for
our-our personal safety,

37:46.098 --> 37:48.064
we did a perimeter check,
and, uh,

37:48.066 --> 37:49.733
he, uh... ran off.

37:49.735 --> 37:50.734
Also, we weren't even

37:50.736 --> 37:53.603
really sure if he was the guy.

37:53.605 --> 37:55.705
Why the hell would he escape
if he's the wrong guy?

37:55.707 --> 37:57.140
Well, we're sort of

37:57.142 --> 37:58.875
still trying to
figure that one out.
- Yeah.

37:58.877 --> 38:00.477
We're gonna
hunt for him today.

38:00.479 --> 38:01.645
Uh, but we just
wanted, uh...

38:01.647 --> 38:03.713
Well, we just wanted
to give you an update.

38:03.715 --> 38:05.148
I'm-I'm sorry, captain.

38:05.150 --> 38:08.318
I know the district
was looking for a big bust.

38:08.320 --> 38:10.920
Yeah, well, things may have
changed a little there.

38:10.922 --> 38:14.291
<i>Gideon is down at the mayor's
office with Murphy right now.</i>

38:14.293 --> 38:16.660
Morning.

38:16.662 --> 38:19.629
Before we begin,
I was told

38:19.631 --> 38:21.665
that you have something
urgent to tell me.

38:21.667 --> 38:23.633
I do, I do, I do. Uh...

38:23.635 --> 38:25.335
This is kind of awkward now.

38:25.337 --> 38:27.337
- What is?
- Well, I...

38:27.339 --> 38:29.005
I should have asked
about this before.

38:29.007 --> 38:31.241
I did it again;
I asked some reporters to come

38:31.243 --> 38:33.009
and do a press
conference

38:33.011 --> 38:34.644
after we're done,
so I just wanted

38:34.646 --> 38:37.180
to talk to you about that.

38:37.182 --> 38:39.416
Well, we don't have
anything to talk about.

38:39.418 --> 38:43.353
You see, I-I'm done
being played by you.

38:43.355 --> 38:47.857
And I'm also done
with your publicity stunts.

38:47.859 --> 38:49.759
This is not a stunt.
This is not a stunt.

38:50.929 --> 38:53.697
Have you ever heard
of the drug hi-town?

38:53.699 --> 38:55.965
If you haven't, you haven't
been paying attention.

38:55.967 --> 38:58.635
It's killed
at least 32 people.

38:58.637 --> 39:01.104
And mostly kids.
We're well aware
of what hi-town is,

39:01.106 --> 39:02.472
thank you.

39:02.474 --> 39:06.209
We're also aware that your bust
resulted in a bad arrest.

39:06.211 --> 39:08.311
Actually, there's been
new developments in that case.

39:08.313 --> 39:10.947
We took down marcos Cruz's
cook lab last night,

39:10.949 --> 39:13.283
and arrested him for
kidnapping and attempted murder.

39:13.285 --> 39:14.551
So no more

39:14.553 --> 39:16.119
hi-town in chi-town.

39:16.121 --> 39:17.120
That's...

39:18.223 --> 39:19.622
Hence the-the press conference,

39:19.624 --> 39:21.958
which, it's gonna be out
in the hallway when we're done.

39:21.960 --> 39:23.226
So we're gonna do that again.

39:23.228 --> 39:24.994
I think so, yeah.
So what should I say?

39:24.996 --> 39:28.331
I could say that your office
is unraveling this bust,

39:28.333 --> 39:30.700
all right, as part
of your ongoing campaign

39:30.702 --> 39:32.736
against the 13th.

39:32.738 --> 39:35.739
Or I can say that we really
appreciate your support

39:35.741 --> 39:37.240
in our victory yesterday.

39:37.242 --> 39:39.142
I don't know.
What do you think?

39:40.545 --> 39:43.313
I think you're a son of a...

39:43.315 --> 39:45.548
This is blackmail.
It's blackmail.

39:45.550 --> 39:46.816
Now, Scott,

39:46.818 --> 39:48.418
to be fair,

39:48.420 --> 39:50.954
you said that I should
come to this meeting prepared.

39:53.091 --> 39:55.358
<i>And I would like to thank</i>

39:55.360 --> 39:58.361
my good friend mayor salgado
for all of his support.

39:58.363 --> 40:01.698
Mr. Reeves, how exactly has the
mayor helped the investigation?

40:01.700 --> 40:04.601
Oh, God, how hasn't he,
is more like it.

40:04.603 --> 40:06.770
Listen, it's no secret
that we've had our bumps,

40:06.772 --> 40:08.538
but at this point,

40:08.540 --> 40:10.607
I'm just glad to have
a partner at city hall.

40:10.609 --> 40:11.841
Does this mean that those rumors

40:11.843 --> 40:14.077
of legal issues
at the 13th are untrue?

40:17.549 --> 40:19.115
Uh, absolutely not.

40:19.117 --> 40:21.885
No, no, no,
we're-we're satisfied that

40:21.887 --> 40:25.855
the 13th district is on firm
legal ground in this case.

40:25.857 --> 40:28.425
And we also appreciate
that fact that

40:28.427 --> 40:30.794
they have
followed our lead

40:30.796 --> 40:33.963
in fighting the scourge
of drugs in this city.

40:35.901 --> 40:38.535
Well, congratulations.
You won.

40:38.537 --> 40:41.471
I wasn't trying to win, Scott.
I was just doing my job.

40:41.473 --> 40:43.873
For him?

40:43.875 --> 40:45.375
For the district.

40:45.377 --> 40:47.977
Right, the district,
of course.

40:47.979 --> 40:49.479
Your real family.

40:49.481 --> 40:53.450
Unlike the one
you broke up.

40:53.452 --> 40:54.984
You are unbelievable.

40:54.986 --> 40:58.054
But if you really
want to go there...

40:58.056 --> 41:00.990
I want to introduce
the lead detective on the case.

41:00.992 --> 41:02.926
Without her,
we would not be here.

41:02.928 --> 41:05.428
Murphy, could you come
over here for a second?

41:05.430 --> 41:08.998
People talk about how much money
I spend in the 13th district.

41:09.000 --> 41:11.000
And by people, I mean
mostly my business manager

41:11.002 --> 41:13.169
and the board of directors.

41:13.171 --> 41:14.838
But the truth is...

41:16.775 --> 41:20.276
The truth is you can't
even begin to put a price

41:20.278 --> 41:23.413
on hard-working cops
like detective Theresa Murphy.

41:24.516 --> 41:26.349
But what is
that price tag, sir?

41:26.351 --> 41:28.251
Well...

41:28.253 --> 41:30.820
♪<i> They're only voices</i>
<i>in the wind</i> ♪

41:30.822 --> 41:33.890
